    <text type="petition">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01003.001.jpg"/>
                        
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">                
                                
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">                   
                
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName>
                            Clerk of the Circuit Court for the <placeName>District of Col</placeName></salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p><persName>Thomas Marshall</persName> of <placeName>Prince Georges County Maryland</placeName> having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned and having refused or neglected to file in your office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the act of Congress, entitled "An act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>, approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16th 1862</date>. You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12th 1862</date>.</p>
                    <p>The said <persName>Caroline Lewis</persName> was a resident of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> on the <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date> &amp; had been for five years previous and with the consent of said <persName>Thomas Marshall</persName>.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>height</cell>
                            <cell>Remarks</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Caroline Lewis</persName></cell>
                            <cell>27 years</cell>
                            <cell>female</cell>
                            <cell><space atLeast="1"/></cell>
                            <cell>Dark brown color</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Caroline Lewis</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness<lb/>
                        <signed><persName>Henry Olive</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01003.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>paid</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Caroline Lewis</persName></ab>
                        <ab>Schedule</ab>
                        <ab><hi rend="underline">Amended Act</hi>.</ab>
                        </div3>
                        <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 89</ab>
                        </div3>
                        <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><hi rend="underline"><persName>Thomas Marshall</persName></hi></ab>
                    </div3>
                                        
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <p>The Commissioners, satisfied on the testimony of <persName>Dennis B. Lyles</persName> of the truth of the within statement order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <ab><date when="1862-09-10">Sept. 10. 1862</date></ab>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk to the Commissioners</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> issued <choice><abbr>Idfd</abbr><expan>Identified</expan></choice> by <persName>Jas H Bradley Jr</persName>.</ab>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01003.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-09-10">Sept 9</date>.</dateline>
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Caroline Lewis</persName></ab>
                    <ab><choice><abbr>Servt</abbr><expan>Servant</expan></choice> of <persName>Thomas Marshall</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Dennis B. Lyles</persName> sworn. I know the facts as stated in schedule to be true. Servant belonged to Mr <persName>Marshall</persName> and has lived here some years &amp; was here <date when="1862-04-16">16 April</date> last &amp; since with consent of the owner.</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>Testimony to be laid before <choice><abbr>comms</abbr><expan>commissioners</expan></choice>. (only one now present)</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><date when="1862-09-10">Sept 10</date> Certificate ordered &amp; sent</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01003.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Caroline Lewis</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-09-10">Sept 10</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
    </text>
